# ============================================================================
# public/.assetsignore  ->  copied by `next build` to out/.assetsignore
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Wrangler reads this file (gitignore syntax) from the assets directory and
# EXCLUDES matching files from the Workers static-asset manifest.
#
# WHY: Cloudflare Workers caps static assets at 100,000 files per version
# (Paid plan; error 10304). On 2026-07-23 the 16-locale export crossed the
# cap (manifest 106,377). The single largest safely-removable category is the
# Next.js App Router RSC payload written next to every page as index.txt
# (~33,700 files at 16 locales, one per route per locale).
#
# EFFECT of excluding them: the client router's soft-navigation prefetch
# (which fetches <route>/index.txt) gets a 404 and Next.js falls back to a
# normal full-page navigation. For a static content site this is a cosmetic
# degradation (MPA-style navigation); HTML, SEO, search (pagefind), OG
# images, the machine-legible .md twins, robots.txt, security.txt and
# llms.txt are all unaffected -- none of those are named index.txt.
#
# Manifest after exclusion: ~72,700 of 100,000 (~27K headroom).
# Decision package with the strategic options lives in concord:
# canon/PKG-asset-budget-2026-07-23.md. (D-19)
# ============================================================================
**/index.txt
